      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Blockages in the pitot tube can be caused by a variety of factors, including ice accumulation, debris, and even the occasional curious bird or insect. In cold weather, ice can form on the pitot tube, reducing airflow and affecting the accuracy of the airspeed reading. Similarly, if the tube is obstructed by a piece of ice or a block of snow, it can reduce the pressure reading, leading to incorrect airspeed indications. In warmer climates, debris like leaves or small twigs can accumulate on the tube, causing blockages and errors.",
